{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Electric|type2=Normal}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Electric|prevnum=694|prev=Helioptile|nextnum=696|next=Tyrunt|roundleft=tl|roundright=tr}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Heliolisk}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Heliolisk\n|jname=エレザード\n|tmname=Elezard\n|jtranslit=Erezādo\n|category=Generator\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Electric\n|type2=Normal\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Dry Skin\n|ability2=Sand Veil\n|abilityd=Solar Power\n|ndex=695\n|karea=Coastal\n|kdex=047\n|height-ftin=3\'03"\n|height-m=1.0\n|weight-lbs=46.3\n|weight-kg=21.0\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Monster\n|egggroup2=Dragon\n|eggcycles=20\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|gendercode=127\n|expyield=168\n|evtotal=2\n|evsp=1\n|evsa=1\n|color=Yellow\n|catchrate=75\n|body=06\n|pokefordex=heliolisk\n|generation=6\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Heliolisk\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'エレザード\'\'\' \'\'Elezard\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Electric|Normal}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation VI]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] from {{p|Helioptile}} when exposed to a [[Sun Stone]].\n\n==Biology==\n[[File:Clemont Heliolisk collar.png|thumb|250px|left|Heliolisk extending its collar]]\nHeliolisk is a bipedal Pokémon that resembles a yellow lizard. Its head is mostly black with a yellow lower jaw. It has blue eyes with a pointed spike over each. Covering its neck is a black frill with orange spikes around the rim. This frill can be raised to frame its head if needed. Its hands and feet are black with three digits each and there is an orange band with triangular markings around each leg. It has a long, tapering tail that is orange and then black at the tip.\n\nHeliolisk can generate sufficient electricity to power a skyscraper, simply by flaring open its frill. This electric energy can be used to stimulates its muscles, which boosts the strength in its legs. This allows it to sprint a hundred yards in five seconds. Heliolisk and its pre-evolution, {{p|Helioptile}} are the [[Signature move|only known Pokémon]] capable of learning {{m|Electrify}}.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Clemont Heliolisk.png|left|thumb|250px|Heliolisk in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\n====[[Clemont\'s Heliolisk]]====\n{{an|Clemont}} owns a Heliolisk that he mainly uses for Gym battles. Instead of taking it with him on his {{pkmn|journey}}, he left it with [[Clembot]] so it could use it for [[Gym]] {{pkmn|battle}}s while he is away. It debuted in \'\'[[XY009|Clemont\'s Got a Secret!]]\'\'. Clembot used it in its battle against Clemont and his {{TP|Clemont|Bunnelby}}, and lost. Clemont later used Heliolisk in a Gym match against {{Ash}}; it battled {{AP|Goodra}} before being defeated by {{AP|Hawlucha}}. Heliolisk reappeared in \'\'[[XY132|A Towering Takeover!]]\'\', where it assisted in the battle against [[Team Flare]].\n\n===Minor appearances===\nA Heliolisk appeared in a fantasy in \'\'[[XY020|Breaking Titles at the Chateau!]]\'\'.\n\nA Heliolisk appeared in \'\'[[XY031|The Cave of Trials!]]\'\', evolving from a {{p|Helioptile}} using a [[Sun Stone]].\n\nA Heliolisk appeared in \'\'[[XY060|A Showcase Debut!]]\'\', under the ownership of a [[Pokémon Performer]] competing in the [[Coumarine City]] [[Pokémon Showcase]].\n\nA Heliolisk appeared in \'\'[[XY073|A Fashionable Battle!]]\'\'.\n\nA Heliolisk appeared in \'\'[[XY078|Lights! Camera! Pika!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Frank]]. Frank used Heliolisk alongside {{p|Swirlix}} and {{p|Magnemite}} to provide the lighting whilst filming his movies.\n\nA Heliolisk appeared in \'\'[[XY105|Party Dancecapades!]]\'\', under the ownership of a Pokémon Performer attending [[Monsieur Pierre]]\'s dance party.\n\nTwo Heliolisk appeared in \'\'[[XY138|The First Day of the Rest of Your Life!]]\'\', each under the ownership of a different Trainer.\n\nAn image of a Heliolisk appeared on {{Ash}}\'s [[Rotom Pokédex]] in \'\'[[SM007|That\'s Why the Litten is a Scamp!]]\'\'.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Kalos}}\n{{Animedexbody|XY009|Heliolisk|Ash\'s Pokédex|Heliolisk, the Generator Pokémon and the evolved form of Helioptile. Heliolisk produces enough electricity to power a large building and recharges by spreading its frills.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'XY\'\'|Kalos}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Clemont Heliolisk Adventures.png|thumb|150px|Heliolisk in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In Pokémon Adventures manga===\n{{main|Clemont\'s Heliolisk}}\n[[Clemont]]\'s Heliolisk was kept hostage by [[Xerosic]] in \'\'[[PAXY19|Gathering Klefki]]\'\'.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Heliolisk (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=electric|type2=normal}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|num1=047|label1=Coastal|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=They flare their frills and generate energy. A single Heliolisk can generate sufficient electricity to power a skyscraper.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=It stimulates its muscles with electricity, boosting the strength in its legs and enabling it to run 100 yards in five seconds.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Omega Ruby|t=FFF|entry=They flare their frills and generate energy. A single Heliolisk can generate sufficient electricity to power a skyscraper.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|t=FFF|v=Alpha Sapphire|entry=It stimulates its muscles with electricity, boosting the strength in its legs and enabling it to run 100 yards in five seconds.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VII|reg1=Alola|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/NE|[[Generation VII]]}}\n|}\n|}\n[[Category:Pokémon in the Galar Pokédex]]<!--\n{{Dex/Gen/1|gen=VIII|reg1=Galar|num1=???}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Sword|v2=Shield|entry=TBD}}\n|}\n|}-->\n{{Dex/Footer}}\n\n===Game locations===\n{{Availability/Header|type=electric|type2=normal}}\n{{Availability/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Availability/Gen|gen=VI}}\n{{Availability/Entry2|v=X|v2=Y|t=FFF|area=[[Evolution|Evolve]] {{p|Helioptile}}}}\n{{Availability/Entry2/None||v=Omega Ruby|v2=Alpha Sap