Pokémon to have more than five hangul characters in its Korean name.\n* Heliolisk and its pre-evolved form are the only Pokémon to have three possible {{Abilities}} ({{a|Dry Skin}}, {{a|Sand Veil}}, and {{a|Solar Power}}) that gets affected by three different weather conditions ({{weather|rain}}, {{weather|sandstorm}}, and {{weather|harsh sunlight}}, respectively).\n** They are also the only Pokémon with Solar Power that cannot learn {{m|Solar Beam}} or {{m|Sunny Day}}.\n\n===Origin===\nHeliolisk is likely based on a {{wp|Chlamydosaurus|frilled-neck lizard}}, because of its notable ability to expand its frill. With its frill fully expanded, Heliolisk also resembles the {{wp|sun}} itself when viewed from the front; its black coloration may possibly be a reference to {{wp|solar eclipse}}s. It may also be based on the {{wp|spotted salamander}}, a salamander that has the ability to {{wp|photosynthesize}}. Its ability to learn Surf may be a reference to the {{wp|common basilisk}}, a reptile capable of running on water for short distances. Heliolisk\'s ability to convert solar energy into electricity along with its title as the Generator Pokémon suggest that it may have been inspired by the {{wp|solar power generation system}}. Its French name suggests it may be based on the {{wp|iguana}}. Additionally, it shares few resemblances to the {{wp|leopard gecko}} and the {{wp|Dilophosaurus|Dilophosaurus}} a genus of theropod with two crests on its head, that is commonly yet inaccurately depicted with frill on its neck.\n\n====Name origin====\nHeliolisk is a combination of ἥλιος \'\'{{wp|helios}}\'\' (Ancient Greek for sun), \'\'{{wp|basilisk}}\'\', and possibly \'\'{{wp|obelisk}}\'\', an ancient Egyptian monument that represented a ray of sunlight piercing the clouds and hitting the ground at a ninety-degree angle.\n\nElezard may be a combination of \'\'{{wp|elekiter}}\'\', エリマキトカゲ \'\'erimaki tokage\'\' (frill-necked lizard), and \'\'lézard\'\' (French for lizard).\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=electric|type2=normal\n|ja=エレザード \'\'Elezard\'\'|jameaning=From \'\'{{wp|elekiter}}\'\', {{tt|エリマキトカゲ \'\'erimaki tokage\'\'|frill-necked lizard}}, \'\'{{tt|lézard|French for lizard}}\'\', and \'\'lizard\'\'\n|fr=Iguolta|frmeaning=From \'\'iguana\'\' and \'\'{{wp|Alessandro Volta|Volta}}\'\'\n|es=Heliolisk|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Elezard|demeaning=Same as Japanese name\n|it=Heliolisk|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=일레도리자드 \'\'Illedorijadeu\'\'|komeaning=From {{tt|일(日) \'\'il\'\'|day, sun}}, \'\'electric\'\', {{tt|\'\'elekiter\'\'|에레키테루}}, {{tt|목도리도마뱀 \'\'mokdori\'domabaem\'\'|frilled-neck lizard}}, and {{tt|\'\'lizard\'\'|리자드}}\n|zh_cmn=電傘查特 \'\'Diànsǎnchátè\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=From {{tt|電 \'\'diàn\'\'|electricity}}, {{tt|傘蜥蜴 \'\'sǎnxīyì\'\'|frilled-neck lizard}}, and {{tt|查特 \'\'chátè\'\'|Partial transliteration of Japanese name}}\n|zh_yue=電傘查特 \'\'Dihnsaanchàhdahk\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=From {{tt|電 \'\'dihn\'\'|electricity}}, {{tt|傘蜥蜴 \'\'saansīkjihk \'\'|frilled-neck lizard}}, and {{tt|查特 \'\'chàhdahk\'\'|Partial transliteration of Japanese name}}\n|hi=हीलियोलिस्क \'\'Heliolisk\'\'|himeaning=Transcription of English name\n|ru=Хелиолиск \'\'Kheliolisk\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n{{-}}\n\n==Related articles==\n* [[Clemont\'s Heliolisk]]\n\n==External links==\n\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Electric|type2=Normal}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Electric|prevnum=694|prev=Helioptile|nextnum=696|next=Tyrunt}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[de:Elezard]]\n[[es:Heliolisk]]\n[[fr:Iguolta]]\n[[it:Heliolisk]]\n[[ja:エレザード]]\n[[zh:光电伞蜥]]'}